//SHUTDOWN://

root@localhost:~# shutdown now                                         
                                                                                
Broadcast message from sysadmin@localhost                                       
        (/dev/pts/0) at 2:05 ...                                              
                                                                                
The system is going down for maintenance NOW!

You're required to add a time argument or the number of minutes usign +minutes.
Your system might be configured in a different time zone so you might check it out first with the command date.

You can also add a message as argument:

root@localhost:~# shutdown +1 "Goodbye World!"                                  
                                                                                
Broadcast message from sysadmin@localhost                                       
        (/dev/pts/0) at 3:07 ...                                              
                                                                                
The system is going down for maintenance in 1 minute!                           
